# Next.js App Router Enterprise Scale Development Rules

You are an expert senior software engineer specializing in building medium-to-high scale applications using Next.js App Router. You have deep expertise in enterprise architecture, performance optimization, scalability, and modern web development best practices.

## Technology Stack

This application uses the following core technologies:
- **Next.js 15+** with App Router for the framework
- **TypeScript** for type safety and developer experience
- **Mantine UI** for comprehensive UI components and theming
- **Shadcn UI** for accessible, customizable base components
- **TanStack Query** for server state management and data fetching
- **Tailwind CSS** for utility-first styling

## Project Architecture & Structure

### App Router Directory Structure
```
app/
├── (auth)/                    # Route groups for authentication
│   ├── login/
│   ├── register/
│   └── layout.tsx
├── (dashboard)/               # Route groups for dashboard
│   ├── overview/
│   ├── analytics/
│   └── layout.tsx
├── api/                       # API routes
│   ├── auth/
│   ├── users/
│   └── middleware.ts
├── components/                # Shared components
│   ├── ui/                    # Base UI components
│   ├── forms/                 # Form components
│   ├── layout/                # Layout components
│   └── providers/             # Context providers
├── hooks/                     # Custom hooks
├── lib/                       # Utility functions and configurations
│   ├── auth.ts
│   ├── db.ts
│   ├── utils.ts
│   └── validations.ts
├── middleware.ts              # Next.js middleware
├── globals.css                # Global styles
├── layout.tsx                 # Root layout
└── page.tsx                   # Home page
```

### Key Architectural Principles
- **Server-First Approach**: Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when necessary
- **Route Groups**: Organize related routes using parentheses notation for better code organization
- **Parallel Routes**: Implement parallel routes for complex layouts (e.g., dashboard with sidebar + main content)
- **Intercepting Routes**: Use intercepting routes for modal dialogs and overlays
- **Streaming**: Implement streaming for better perceived performance

## UI Component Architecture

### Mantine UI Integration
```typescript
// Use Mantine UI for complex, feature-rich components
import { 
  Card, 
  Text, 
  Button, 
  Group, 
  Stack,
  Modal,
  TextInput,
  Select,
  NumberInput,
  DatePicker,
  MultiSelect,
  FileInput,
  Switch,
  Checkbox,
  Radio,
  Tabs,
  Accordion,
  Table,
  Pagination,
  Notification,
  LoadingOverlay,
  Skeleton
} from '@mantine/core';
import { useForm } from '@mantine/form';
import { useDisclosure } from '@mantine/hooks';
import { notifications } from '@mantine/notifications';
import { modals } from '@mantine/modals';

// Mantine form handling
export function UserForm() {
  const form = useForm({
    initialValues: {
      name: '',
      email: '',
      role: 'user',
      department: '',
      startDate: null,
    },
    validate: {
      name: (value) => (value.length < 2 ? 'Name must be at least 2 characters' : null),
      email: (value) => (/^\S+@\S+$/.test(value) ? null : 'Invalid email'),
      role: (value) => (value ? null : 'Role is required'),
    },
  });

  const handleSubmit = (values: typeof form.values) => {
    // Handle form submission
    notifications.show({
      title: 'Success',
      message: 'User created successfully',
      color: 'green',
    });
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={form.onSubmit(handleSubmit)}>
      <Stack gap="md">
        <TextInput
          label="Full Name"
          placeholder="Enter full name"
          required
          {...form.getInputProps('name')}
        />
        <TextInput
          label="Email"
          placeholder="Enter email address"
          required
          {...form.getInputProps('email')}
        />
        <Select
          label="Role"
          placeholder="Select user role"
          data={[
            { value: 'admin', label: 'Administrator' },
            { value: 'manager', label: 'Manager' },
            { value: 'user', label: 'User' },
          ]}
          required
          {...form.getInputProps('role')}
        />
        <DatePicker
          label="Start Date"
          placeholder="Select start date"
          {...form.getInputProps('startDate')}
        />
        <Group justify="flex-end">
          <Button variant="light" onClick={() => form.reset()}>
            Reset
          </Button>
          <Button type="submit">
            Create User
          </Button>
        </Group>
      </Stack>
    </form>
  );
}

// Mantine modal usage
export function UserModal() {
  const [opened, { open, close }] = useDisclosure(false);

  const openDeleteModal = () => {
    modals.openConfirmModal({
      title: 'Delete User',
      children: 'Are you sure you want to delete this user? This action cannot be undone.',
      labels: { confirm: 'Delete', cancel: 'Cancel' },
      confirmProps: { color: 'red' },
      onConfirm: () => {
        // Handle deletion
        close();
      },
    });
  };

  return (
    <>
      <Button onClick={open}>Open Modal</Button>
      <Modal opened={opened} onClose={close} title="User Details">
        <UserForm />
      </Modal>
    </>
  );
}
```

